  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>A storm made up of sheets of roaring flame appears in a location you choose within range. The area of the storm consists of up to ten 10-foot cubes, which you can arrange as you wish. Each &amp;Reference[cube]{cube} must have at least one face adjacent to the face of another &amp;Reference[cube]{cube}. Each creature in the area must make a &amp;Reference[dex]{Dexterity} saving throw. It takes 7d10 &amp;Reference[fire]{fire} damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>The &amp;Reference[fire]{fire} damages objects in the area and ignites flammable objects that aren't being worn or carried. If you choose, &amp;Reference[plant]{plant} life in the area is unaffected by this spell.</p>\n</div>",
